			UC Irvine Office of the Registrar
		      Schedule of Classes    Tuesday, May 17, 2016

Search Criteria:
    Course Code Range: 1000-1999
    Exclude cancelled courses


Spring Quarter, 2016      Currently in week 8.


   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The petition form is         ###
   ###  available on Student Access.                                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major restrictions for some courses will be removed at noon on   ###
   ###  March 18, 2016.                                                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                     Art

        Enrolled students who do not appear ON TIME for the first day of
        instruction will be dropped from the course at the instructor's
        discretion. Students will be responsible for officially dropping
        the course through WebReg.

        Course material fees are non-refundable, unless the class is
        officially dropped and the student notifies the Department of
        Art administrative office by the MONDAY OF THE THIRD WEEK of the
        quarter. Fees will not be refunded beyond the Monday of the
        third week; no exceptions.

        Students are welcome to enroll in any Art courses when the major
        restrictions are removed. If classes are fully enrolled,
        students are encouraged to enroll in the Wait List, if
        available.

        Instructors will give "drop" codes through the second week of
        classes, and "add" codes through the third week of classes,
        based on availability.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The petition form is         ###
   ###  available on Student Access.                                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major restrictions for some courses will be removed at noon on   ###
   ###  March 18, 2016.                                                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###

        Dance 171 - Dance Workshop, Dance 172 - MFA Concert, Dance 174
        -- Dance Ensemble Performance, Dance 176   Jazz Dance Ensemble
        or Dance 179 - Etude Ensemble, please email BCODES@UCI.EDU.

        To request a B code for all other courses, please contact the
        instructor of record.

   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The petition form is         ###
   ###  available on Student Access.                                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major restrictions for some courses will be removed at noon on   ###
   ###  March 18, 2016.                                                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The petition form is         ###
   ###  available on Student Access.                                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major restrictions for some courses will be removed at noon on   ###
   ###  March 18, 2016.                                                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                    Music

        Students who register in courses in private instrumental and
        vocal lessons (Music 65, 66, 67, 68, 69, 70, 165, 166, 167, 168,
        169, and 170) are assessed a course materials and service fee of
        $500. This fee is refundable if the course is dropped by the end
        of the second week of classes with the following conditions: (1)
        if no lesson has been given, the fee is refundable in full; (2)
        if one lesson has been given, the fee is refundable at the
        pro-rated amount of $444; (3) if two lessons have been given,
        the fee is refundable at the pro-rated amount of $400. Requests
        for a fee reversal should be directed to the Music Department
        office. No fee reversal will be made for courses dropped after
        the end of the second week of classes.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Francisco J. Ayala     ###
   ###  School of Biological Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM     ###
   ###  with the exception of Upper-Division Labs that have a drop       ###
   ###  deadline of MONDAY, MARCH 28th AT 5:00pm. Drops can be made in   ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:OO PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ALL BIOLOGICAL SCIENCE COURSES ARE RESTRICTED UNTIL MARCH 18TH   ###
   ###  AT NOON.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Francisco J. Ayala       ###
   ###  School of Biological Sciences is the end of week 2 at 5PM. Adds  ###
   ###  can be made in WebReg. Students are responsible for all          ###
   ###  materials from the start of the term. Failure to take any exams  ###
   ###  or quizzes, even those given before you have added the course,   ###
   ###  will result in a zero score for each quiz or exam.               ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                             Biological Sciences

        REPEATS and MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: Students who wish to enroll to
        repeat a course will be restricted from enrolling until (Noon) -
        March 18th

        PREREQUISITES: Students who have completed the equivalent of the
        prerequisites at another institution may become eligible to
        enroll in a particular UCI Bio Sci course by completing the form
        on the Bio Sci Student Affairs website:
        http://www.bio.uci.edu/students/undergraduates/course-pre-requisite-clearance-form/
        a minimum of two days before their window opens. Once students
        have had their prerequisites cleared they will remain eligible
        for one quarter, with the exception of Bio 199 (clearance
        remains for the academic year).

        LAB COURSES:

        BIO LAB ENROLLMENT POLICY!!!!

        THERE WILL BE NO DROPS OF ANY BIO SCI UPPER-DIVISION LABS AFTER
        MARCH 28TH at 5:00 PM. This deadline is earlier than the
        Francisco J. Ayala School of Biological Sciences week 2
        deadline.

        MINIMUM GRADE POLICY!!!!!

        Beginning Fall 2010, students must earn a grade of "C-" or above
        to advance to the next Bio core course. For example, you must
        earn a "C-" or better grade in Bio Sci 93 to move onto Bio Sci
        94, 97, 98 and 99.

   ###  School of Biological Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM     ###
   ###  with the exception of Upper-Division Labs that have a drop       ###
   ###  deadline of MONDAY, MARCH 28th AT 5:00pm. Drops can be made in   ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:OO PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ALL BIOLOGICAL SCIENCE COURSES ARE RESTRICTED UNTIL MARCH 18TH   ###
   ###  AT NOON.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Francisco J. Ayala       ###
   ###  School of Biological Sciences is the end of week 2 at 5PM. Adds  ###
   ###  can be made in WebReg. Students are responsible for all          ###
   ###  materials from the start of the term. Failure to take any exams  ###
   ###  or quizzes, even those given before you have added the course,   ###
   ###  will result in a zero score for each quiz or exam.               ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                             Biological Sciences

        REPEATS and MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: Students who wish to enroll to
        repeat a course will be restricted from enrolling until (Noon) -
        March 18th

        PREREQUISITES: Students who have completed the equivalent of the
        prerequisites at another institution may become eligible to
        enroll in a particular UCI Bio Sci course by completing the form
        on the Bio Sci Student Affairs website:
        http://www.bio.uci.edu/students/undergraduates/course-pre-requisite-clearance-form/
        a minimum of two days before their window opens. Once students
        have had their prerequisites cleared they will remain eligible
        for one quarter, with the exception of Bio 199 (clearance
        remains for the academic year).

        LAB COURSES:

        BIO LAB ENROLLMENT POLICY!!!!

        THERE WILL BE NO DROPS OF ANY BIO SCI UPPER-DIVISION LABS AFTER
        MARCH 28TH at 5:00 PM. This deadline is earlier than the
        Francisco J. Ayala School of Biological Sciences week 2
        deadline.

        MINIMUM GRADE POLICY!!!!!

        Beginning Fall 2010, students must earn a grade of "C-" or above
        to advance to the next Bio core course. For example, you must
        earn a "C-" or better grade in Bio Sci 93 to move onto Bio Sci
        94, 97, 98 and 99.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Francisco J. Ayala     ###
   ###  School of Biological Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM     ###
   ###  with the exception of Upper-Division Labs that have a drop       ###
   ###  deadline of MONDAY, MARCH 28th AT 5:00pm. Drops can be made in   ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:OO PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ALL BIOLOGICAL SCIENCE COURSES ARE RESTRICTED UNTIL MARCH 18TH   ###
   ###  AT NOON.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Francisco J. Ayala       ###
   ###  School of Biological Sciences is the end of week 2 at 5PM. Adds  ###
   ###  can be made in WebReg. Students are responsible for all          ###
   ###  materials from the start of the term. Failure to take any exams  ###
   ###  or quizzes, even those given before you have added the course,   ###
   ###  will result in a zero score for each quiz or exam.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                             Biological Sciences

        REPEATS and MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: Students who wish to enroll to
        repeat a course will be restricted from enrolling until (Noon) -
        March 18th

        PREREQUISITES: Students who have completed the equivalent of the
        prerequisites at another institution may become eligible to
        enroll in a particular UCI Bio Sci course by completing the form
        on the Bio Sci Student Affairs website:
        http://www.bio.uci.edu/students/undergraduates/course-pre-requisite-clearance-form/
        a minimum of two days before their window opens. Once students
        have had their prerequisites cleared they will remain eligible
        for one quarter, with the exception of Bio 199 (clearance
        remains for the academic year).

        LAB COURSES:

        BIO LAB ENROLLMENT POLICY!!!!

        THERE WILL BE NO DROPS OF ANY BIO SCI UPPER-DIVISION LABS AFTER
        MARCH 28TH at 5:00 PM. This deadline is earlier than the
        Francisco J. Ayala School of Biological Sciences week 2
        deadline.

        MINIMUM GRADE POLICY!!!!!

        Beginning Fall 2010, students must earn a grade of "C-" or above
        to advance to the next Bio core course. For example, you must
        earn a "C-" or better grade in Bio Sci 93 to move onto Bio Sci
        94, 97, 98 and 99.
       _________________________________________________________________

  ~     http://www.bio.uci.edu/students/undergraduates/research/
  ~ Maximum 5 units per quarter for all independent study
  ~     courses taken under Francisco J. Ayala School of
  ~     Biological Sciences. Student must be in good
  ~     academic standing.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Francisco J. Ayala     ###
   ###  School of Biological Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM     ###
   ###  with the exception of Upper-Division Labs that have a drop       ###
   ###  deadline of MONDAY, MARCH 28th AT 5:00pm. Drops can be made in   ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:OO PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ALL BIOLOGICAL SCIENCE COURSES ARE RESTRICTED UNTIL MARCH 18TH   ###
   ###  AT NOON.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Francisco J. Ayala       ###
   ###  School of Biological Sciences is the end of week 2 at 5PM. Adds  ###
   ###  can be made in WebReg. Students are responsible for all          ###
   ###  materials from the start of the term. Failure to take any exams  ###
   ###  or quizzes, even those given before you have added the course,   ###
   ###  will result in a zero score for each quiz or exam.               ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2015-2016 General Catalogue under each course    ###
   ###  description or at http://plaza.eng.uci.edu. Most major           ###
   ###  restrictions will be lifted at the fee deadline,  March 15,      ###
   ###  2016. Some restrictions will be loosened from major only to      ###
   ###  Engineering major only after the last enrollment window closes.  ###
   ###  Check http://plaza.eng.uci.edu for announcements.                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization, available at ###
   ###  the Engineering Student Affairs Office, REC 305.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Students earning a deficient grade in a prerequisite course      ###
   ###  after enrolling will be dropped after the first week of class.   ###
   ###  Students should address any prior grade issues (NR, I, etc.)     ###
   ###  before the end of Week 1.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ASSISTANCE: If you encounter a schedule problem please email ###
   ###  engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule updates, restriction       ###
   ###  changes, and changes to course capacities at                     ###
   ###  http://plaza.eng.uci.edu                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

Restriction Codes from the 'Rst' column above:
    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    D: Pass/not pass option only
    F: Sophomores only
    I: Seniors only
    J: Upper-division only
    K: Graduate only
    N: School major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only
    X: Separate authorization codes required to add, drop, or change enrollment

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2015-2016 General Catalogue under each course    ###
   ###  description or at http://plaza.eng.uci.edu. Most major           ###
   ###  restrictions will be lifted at the fee deadline,  March 15,      ###
   ###  2016. Some restrictions will be loosened from major only to      ###
   ###  Engineering major only after the last enrollment window closes.  ###
   ###  Check http://plaza.eng.uci.edu for announcements.                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization, available at ###
   ###  the Engineering Student Affairs Office, REC 305.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Students earning a deficient grade in a prerequisite course      ###
   ###  after enrolling will be dropped after the first week of class.   ###
   ###  Students should address any prior grade issues (NR, I, etc.)     ###
   ###  before the end of Week 1.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ASSISTANCE: If you encounter a schedule problem please email ###
   ###  engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule updates, restriction       ###
   ###  changes, and changes to course capacities at                     ###
   ###  http://plaza.eng.uci.edu                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2015-2016 General Catalogue under each course    ###
   ###  description or at http://plaza.eng.uci.edu. Most major           ###
   ###  restrictions will be lifted at the fee deadline,  March 15,      ###
   ###  2016. Some restrictions will be loosened from major only to      ###
   ###  Engineering major only after the last enrollment window closes.  ###
   ###  Check http://plaza.eng.uci.edu for announcements.                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization, available at ###
   ###  the Engineering Student Affairs Office, REC 305.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Students earning a deficient grade in a prerequisite course      ###
   ###  after enrolling will be dropped after the first week of class.   ###
   ###  Students should address any prior grade issues (NR, I, etc.)     ###
   ###  before the end of Week 1.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ASSISTANCE: If you encounter a schedule problem please email ###
   ###  engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule updates, restriction       ###
   ###  changes, and changes to course capacities at                     ###
   ###  http://plaza.eng.uci.edu                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2015-2016 General Catalogue under each course    ###
   ###  description or at http://plaza.eng.uci.edu. Most major           ###
   ###  restrictions will be lifted at the fee deadline,  March 15,      ###
   ###  2016. Some restrictions will be loosened from major only to      ###
   ###  Engineering major only after the last enrollment window closes.  ###
   ###  Check http://plaza.eng.uci.edu for announcements.                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization, available at ###
   ###  the Engineering Student Affairs Office, REC 305.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Students earning a deficient grade in a prerequisite course      ###
   ###  after enrolling will be dropped after the first week of class.   ###
   ###  Students should address any prior grade issues (NR, I, etc.)     ###
   ###  before the end of Week 1.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ASSISTANCE: If you encounter a schedule problem please email ###
   ###  engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule updates, restriction       ###
   ###  changes, and changes to course capacities at                     ###
   ###  http://plaza.eng.uci.edu                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2015-2016 General Catalogue under each course    ###
   ###  description or at http://plaza.eng.uci.edu. Most major           ###
   ###  restrictions will be lifted at the fee deadline,  March 15,      ###
   ###  2016. Some restrictions will be loosened from major only to      ###
   ###  Engineering major only after the last enrollment window closes.  ###
   ###  Check http://plaza.eng.uci.edu for announcements.                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization, available at ###
   ###  the Engineering Student Affairs Office, REC 305.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Students earning a deficient grade in a prerequisite course      ###
   ###  after enrolling will be dropped after the first week of class.   ###
   ###  Students should address any prior grade issues (NR, I, etc.)     ###
   ###  before the end of Week 1.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ASSISTANCE: If you encounter a schedule problem please email ###
   ###  engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule updates, restriction       ###
   ###  changes, and changes to course capacities at                     ###
   ###  http://plaza.eng.uci.edu                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2015-2016 General Catalogue under each course    ###
   ###  description or at http://plaza.eng.uci.edu. Most major           ###
   ###  restrictions will be lifted at the fee deadline,  March 15,      ###
   ###  2016. Some restrictions will be loosened from major only to      ###
   ###  Engineering major only after the last enrollment window closes.  ###
   ###  Check http://plaza.eng.uci.edu for announcements.                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization, available at ###
   ###  the Engineering Student Affairs Office, REC 305.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Students earning a deficient grade in a prerequisite course      ###
   ###  after enrolling will be dropped after the first week of class.   ###
   ###  Students should address any prior grade issues (NR, I, etc.)     ###
   ###  before the end of Week 1.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ASSISTANCE: If you encounter a schedule problem please email ###
   ###  engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule updates, restriction       ###
   ###  changes, and changes to course capacities at                     ###
   ###  http://plaza.eng.uci.edu                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2015-2016 General Catalogue under each course    ###
   ###  description or at http://plaza.eng.uci.edu. Most major           ###
   ###  restrictions will be lifted at the fee deadline,  March 15,      ###
   ###  2016. Some restrictions will be loosened from major only to      ###
   ###  Engineering major only after the last enrollment window closes.  ###
   ###  Check http://plaza.eng.uci.edu for announcements.                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites.  Courses with co-requisites may ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization, available at ###
   ###  the Engineering Student Affairs Office, REC 305.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Students earning a deficient grade in a prerequisite course      ###
   ###  after enrolling will be dropped after the first week of class.   ###
   ###  Students should address any prior grade issues (NR, I, etc.)     ###
   ###  before the end of Week 1.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ASSISTANCE: If you encounter a schedule problem please email ###
   ###  engcasa@uci.edu or check for schedule updates, restriction       ###
   ###  changes, and changes to course capacities at                     ###
   ###  http://plaza.eng.uci.edu                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###

   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Chinese

        Students intending to enroll in a Chinese language class for the
        first time in spring 2016 must complete a placement process.
        First, complete the online survey at
        https://eee.uci.edu/survey/ChineseSurvey to determine if a
        written placement test is needed.

        Next, sign up online for a Faculty Oral Interview scheduled on
        Wednesday, February 24 or Thursday, February 25 at
        https://eee.uci.edu/signupsheet/chineseinterview022402252016.

        Testing will be offered on Tuesday, February 23, 2016. You may
        register for the placement test with the UCI Academic Testing
        Center through their web site,
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/.

        For those who are required to take the written placement test,
        testing will be offered on Tuesday, February 23, 2016. You may
        register for the placement test with the UCI Academic Testing
        Center on their web site http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/.

        Find out your placement and obtain authorization to register at
        the interview.

        For additional test information, contact the UCI Academic
        Testing Center by phone at (949) 824-6207 or by email at
        testcenter@uci.edu. For inquiries about Faculty Oral Interview,
        contact Ruohmei Hsieh, Chinese Language Coordinator at
        rhsieh@uci.edu.

        Students registered in any section of Chinese 1C/1MC, 2C/2MC, or
        3C MUST ATTEND THE FIRST and SECOND class meeting of the course.
        Any student who does not meet this condition will be required to
        drop the class.

                           Comparative Literature

        Students registered in any course offered by the Department of
        Comparative Literature are expected to attend both the FIRST and
        SECOND class meetings of the course or they may be required to
        drop the course.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   English

        Students registered in any course offered by the Department of
        English are expected to attend both the FIRST and SECOND CLASS
        MEETINGS of the course or they may be required to drop the
        course. Please be advised that some English courses will have a
        "B" or "X" restriction starting on the first day of instruction
        and waitlists will be deactivated at that time. You must remove
        yourself from the waitlist before the deactivation or you may
        have enrollment problems. Contact your instructor to determine
        whether or not your course will become restricted on the first
        day of instruction.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                           Film and Media Studies

        Film viewing takes place in the studio sections. Attendance is
        mandatory. Enrollment in lecture and studio, or lecture and
        studio and discussion, where offered, is required for all Film &
        Media Studies courses.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

                                   French

        TO ENROLL IN A FRENCH LANGUAGE CLASS: French placement testing
        is recommended, but not required for students who have
        successfully completed French classes in high school. Contact
        the UCI Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, (949)
        824-6207, or visit their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a placement test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) French exam is eligible to enroll directly into French 2A.
        A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement French exam is eligible to enroll directly into
        French100A; however, full credit will be awarded for French 2C
        if the student wants to take French 2C first for review.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        French, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        Any placement exceptions must have the written approval of the
        French Language Program Director.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.
       _________________________________________________________________

Restriction Codes from the 'Rst' column above:
    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    D: Pass/not pass option only
    I: Seniors only
    J: Upper-division only
    K: Graduate only
    M: Non-major only
    N: School major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

        second week of classes.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   German

        TO ENROLL IN A GERMAN LANGUAGE CLASS: For all German courses
        beyond 1A, placement testing is recommended for students who
        have had previous experience with or instruction in the
        language. Contact the UCI Academic Testing Center at
        testcenter@uci.edu, (949) 824-6207, or visit their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a placement test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) German exam is eligible to enroll directly into German 2A.
        A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement German exam is eligible to enroll directly into German
        100A, 100B or 100C. However, full credit will be awarded for
        German 2C if the student wants to take German 2C first for
        review.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        German, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        For placement-related questions contact Language Program
        Director Professor Glenn S. Levine (glevine@uci.edu).

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

Course Codes 27600 - 28130:
  ~ HUMANITIES CORE (course codes 27600-28130):
  ~ ENROLLMENT PROCEDURE: To insure proper enrollment in
  ~     both the Seminar and Lecture, students must
  ~     enroll in the Lecture first, and the Seminar
  ~     second.
  ~ ATTENDANCE: Students registered in Humanities Core
  ~     are expected to attend both the FIRST and SECOND
  ~     class meetings of the course or they may be
  ~     required to drop the course.
  ~ HUMANITIES CORE ADD/DROP POLICY: ADDS and DROPS must
  ~     be effected PRIOR, to the END of the SECOND WEEK
  ~     OF CLASSES.
  ~ COURSE AUTHORIZATION: All authorization codes for
  ~     Humanities Core sections are obtained from Dawn
  ~     Jenison (djenison@uci.edu) in the Humanities Core
  ~     office (HIB 185), (949)824-1964. Authorization
  ~     codes will NOT be provided by instructors in the
  ~     individual course sections.
  ~ ENROLLMENT EXCEPTIONS: Any exception to the two week
  ~     ADD/DROP deadline must be requested as an
  ~     Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess
  ~     system after second week for ADDs and DROPs and
  ~     requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Course Codes 27600 - 28130:
  ~ HUMANITIES CORE (course codes 27600-28130):

Course Codes 28100 - 28130:
  ~ Humanities Core H1C sections are open to students in
  ~     the Campuswide Honors Program ONLY AND must be
  ~     taken for a letter grade. During the first two
  ~     weeks of the quarter, HUMAN H1C will have a "B"
  ~     restriction. Please contact the Campuswide Honors
  ~     Program at (949)824-8440 to obtain authorization
  ~     codes for HUMAN H1C.

Course Codes 27600 - 28130:
  ~ ENROLLMENT PROCEDURE: To insure proper enrollment in
  ~     both the Seminar and Lecture, students must
  ~     enroll in the Lecture first, and the Seminar
  ~     second.

Course Codes 28100 - 28130:
  ~ Students must add the Lecture first, then the Seminar
  ~     second to add the course.

Course Codes 27600 - 28130:
  ~ ATTENDANCE: Students registered in Humanities Core
  ~     are expected to attend both the FIRST and SECOND
  ~     class meetings of the course or they may be
  ~     required to drop the course.
  ~ HUMANITIES CORE ADD/DROP POLICY: ADDS and DROPS must
  ~     be effected PRIOR, to the END of the SECOND WEEK
  ~     OF CLASSES.
  ~ COURSE AUTHORIZATION: All authorization codes for
  ~     Humanities Core sections are obtained from Dawn
  ~     Jenison (djenison@uci.edu) in the Humanities Core
  ~     office (HIB 185), (949)824-1964. Authorization
  ~     codes will NOT be provided by instructors in the
  ~     individual course sections.
  ~ ENROLLMENT EXCEPTIONS: Any exception to the two week
  ~     ADD/DROP deadline must be requested as an
  ~     Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess
  ~     system after second week for ADDs and DROPs and
  ~     requires approval of the Undergraduate Dean.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Italian

        TO ENROLL IN A ITALIAN LANGUAGE CLASS: Italian placement testing
        is recommended, but not required for students who have
        successfully completed Italian classes in high school. Contact
        the UCI Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, (949)
        824-6207, or visit their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a placement test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) Italian exam is eligible to enroll directly into Italian
        2A. A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement Italian exam is eligible to enroll directly into
        Italian 100A; however, full credit will be awarded for Italian
        2C if the student wants to take Italian 2C first for review.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        Italian, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        Any placement exceptions must have the written approval of the
        Italian Language Program Director.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.
       _________________________________________________________________

                                  Japanese

        Students registered in any section of Japanese 1C, 2C, or 3C
        MUST ATTEND THE FIRST and SECOND class meeting of the course.
        Any student who does not meet this condition will be required to
        drop the class.

        Students wanting to enroll in a Japanese 1C, 2C, or 3C class for
        the first time at UCI in spring 2016 are required to take the
        Japanese placement test on Wednesday, February 24, 2016. An oral
        interview is also required to finalize your placement. The
        interview is scheduled at 12:00-1:00pm on Thursday, February 25
        in HIB 379. It is on a walk-in basis and an appointment is not
        required. If you have any further concern regarding the
        interview, contact the academic coordinator of Japanese language
        program, Hidemi Riggs at hriggs@uci.edu.

        Contact the UCI Academic Testing Center through their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/, by phone at (949) 824-6207,
        or by email at testcenter@uci.edu for details about test
        registration.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, email hriggs@uci.edu to
        obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of the
        class.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Korean

        TO ENROLL IN A KOREAN LANGUAGE CLASS:

        Students intending to enroll in a Korean language class for the
        first time in Spring 2016, MUST take a placement test. Testing
        will be offered Monday, February 29, 2016. Students may register
        for this exam with the UCI Academic Testing Center through their
        web site, http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu. For additional
        information, contact the UCI Academic Testing Center at
        testcenter@uci.edu or call 949-824-6207.

        After the test, bring the written test result and the language
        background survey with you to the Faculty Oral Interview offered
        on Thursday, March 3, 2016, 2:00p.m.-4:00p.m., at HIB 448.
        Please access to the EEE Signup Sheet to make an appointment for
        the interview at https://eee.uci.edu/signupsheet/0303korean.  Be
        sure to bring your language background survey form, test result,
        and your student ID card with you at the time of the interview.
        For inquiries about the Faculty Oral Interview, contact
        Hyun-young Hyun, Korean Language Program Coordinator at
        hhyun@uci.edu.

        Students registered in any section of Korean 1C, 1KC, 2C, 2KC,
        or 3C MUST ATTEND THE FIRST and SECOND class meeting of the
        course. Any student who does not meet this condition will be
        required to drop the class.

                             Literary Journalism

        Satisfaction of the UC Entry Level Writing Requirement is
        PREREQUISITE to all LIT JRN courses offered by the Department of
        English.

        Students registered in any LIT JRN course offered by the
        Department of English are expected to attend both the FIRST and
        SECOND CLASS MEETINGS of the course or they may be required to
        drop the course.

        If a course has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Literary
        Journalism Program to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the
        grading option of the course.

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                             Literary Journalism

        Satisfaction of the UC Entry Level Writing Requirement is
        PREREQUISITE to all LIT JRN courses offered by the Department of
        English.

        Students registered in any LIT JRN course offered by the
        Department of English are expected to attend both the FIRST and
        SECOND CLASS MEETINGS of the course or they may be required to
        drop the course.

        If a course has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Literary
        Journalism Program to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the
        grading option of the course.

                                   Spanish

        For all placement-related questions, especially regarding
        enrollment in lower division Spanish language courses, please
        consult the Spanish Placement Table at
        http://www.humanities.uci.edu/spanishandportuguese/language/placement.php

        Students who receive a placement of "Spanish 3B/101A" on the
        placement exam and wish to enroll in upper division courses
        without completing Spanish 3B must complete the Prerequisite
        Exemption Petition form at
        https://copa.humanities.uci.edu/spanudpet/index.php

        Contact the Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, at
        (949) 824-6207, or visit their Web site at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a test.

        STUDENTS ARE REQUIRED TO ATTEND THE FIRST TWO CLASS MEETINGS.
        Enrolled students who do not attend the first two class meetings
        may be dropped from the instructor's roll. These students will
        be required to formally drop the course.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                                   Spanish

        For all placement-related questions, especially regarding
        enrollment in lower division Spanish language courses, please
        consult the Spanish Placement Table at
        http://www.humanities.uci.edu/spanishandportuguese/language/placement.php

        Students who receive a placement of "Spanish 3B/101A" on the
        placement exam and wish to enroll in upper division courses
        without completing Spanish 3B must complete the Prerequisite
        Exemption Petition form at
        https://copa.humanities.uci.edu/spanudpet/index.php

        Contact the Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, at
        (949) 824-6207, or visit their Web site at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a test.

        STUDENTS ARE REQUIRED TO ATTEND THE FIRST TWO CLASS MEETINGS.
        Enrolled students who do not attend the first two class meetings
        may be dropped from the instructor's roll. These students will
        be required to formally drop the course.
