   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Writing

        PLEASE BE ADVISED

        Writing courses will have a "B" or "X" restriction starting on
        the first day of instruction. Students will need to contact the
        instructor to obtain an authorization code to add, drop, or
        change the grading option for the class.

        Waitlists for Writing 30, 31, 37, 39A, 39B, 39C, 91, 101W and
        139W will be deactivated on the first day of instruction.

        ADD/DROP Policy during the FIRST and SECOND week of Instruction
        for Composition Courses

        Students who are permitted to add or drop a Writing Course must
        obtain an authorization code from the instructor of the section.
        Students WILL NOT be authorized to add a Writing Course after
        week 1.

        After the second week of the term students will no longer be
        permitted to drop except through petition.

        Students enrolled in Entry-Level and Lower-Division Writing
        courses are REQUIRED TO ATTEND THE FIRST CLASS MEETING. Enrolled
        students who do not show up on the first day WILL BE DROPPED
        from the instructor's roll and their spot will be given away.
        These students will still be required to formally drop the
        course.

        For more information about Composition courses and
        prerequisites, visit the Program website:
        http://comp.humanities.uci.edu/

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION DEADLINE: The Donald Bren School of ###
   ###  Information and Computer Sciences STRICTLY adheres to the campus ###
   ###  deadline of 5:00pm on Friday of Week 2 for both undergraduate    ###
   ###  AND graduate level courses.                                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception Requests: After the add/drop/change grade   ###
   ###  option deadline, an online Enrollment Exception must be          ###
   ###  submitted. Approval of enrollment exception requests is not      ###
   ###  automatic. Students should be prepared to submit documentation   ###
   ###  for any enrollment exception request. For more information:      ###
   ###  https://www.reg.uci.edu/enrollment/adc/exceptions.html           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: Prerequisites are strictly enforced. The School   ###
   ###  WILL DROP students from courses for which they have not          ###
   ###  satisfied prerequisites. If you find you have been dropped from  ###
   ###  a course, please check the course prerequisites and contact the  ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs Office                                       ###
   ###  (http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/index.php) BEFORE enrolling in ###
   ###  the course again. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a space in the class.                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT RESTRICTION: Students are not allowed to repeat a course  ###
   ###  if they previously received a grade of C or better.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DISCUSSIONS & LABS: Unless otherwise specified by the course     ###
   ###  instructor, discussion and lab sections begin meeting AFTER the  ###
   ###  first lecture.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate students  ###
   ###  may enroll in undergraduate courses with permission and pending  ###
   ###  availability of seating.  Graduate students enrolled without     ###
   ###  prior approval will be dropped.                                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students may enroll in graduate level courses with the           ###
   ###  instructor's consent, if seats are available. No graduate course ###
   ###  taken as an undergraduate will count toward a graduate degree    ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

Restriction Codes from the 'Rst' column above:
    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    I: Seniors only
    K: Graduate only
    N: School major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only
    X: Separate authorization codes required to add, drop, or change enrollment
			UC Irvine Office of the Registrar
		      Schedule of Classes    Tuesday, May 17, 2016

Search Criteria:
    Course Code Range: 35000-35999
    Exclude cancelled courses


Spring Quarter, 2016      Currently in week 8.


   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION DEADLINE: The Donald Bren School of ###
   ###  Information and Computer Sciences STRICTLY adheres to the campus ###
   ###  deadline of 5:00pm on Friday of Week 2 for both undergraduate    ###
   ###  AND graduate level courses.                                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception Requests: After the add/drop/change grade   ###
   ###  option deadline, an online Enrollment Exception must be          ###
   ###  submitted. Approval of enrollment exception requests is not      ###
   ###  automatic. Students should be prepared to submit documentation   ###
   ###  for any enrollment exception request. For more information:      ###
   ###  https://www.reg.uci.edu/enrollment/adc/exceptions.html           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: Prerequisites are strictly enforced. The School   ###
   ###  WILL DROP students from courses for which they have not          ###
   ###  satisfied prerequisites. If you find you have been dropped from  ###
   ###  a course, please check the course prerequisites and contact the  ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs Office                                       ###
   ###  (http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/index.php) BEFORE enrolling in ###
   ###  the course again. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a space in the class.                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT RESTRICTION: Students are not allowed to repeat a course  ###
   ###  if they previously received a grade of C or better.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DISCUSSIONS & LABS: Unless otherwise specified by the course     ###
   ###  instructor, discussion and lab sections begin meeting AFTER the  ###
   ###  first lecture.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate students  ###
   ###  may enroll in undergraduate courses with permission and pending  ###
   ###  availability of seating.  Graduate students enrolled without     ###
   ###  prior approval will be dropped.                                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students may enroll in graduate level courses with the           ###
   ###  instructor's consent, if seats are available. No graduate course ###
   ###  taken as an undergraduate will count toward a graduate degree    ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION DEADLINE: The Donald Bren School of ###
   ###  Information and Computer Sciences STRICTLY adheres to the campus ###
   ###  deadline of 5:00pm on Friday of Week 2 for both undergraduate    ###
   ###  AND graduate level courses.                                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception Requests: After the add/drop/change grade   ###
   ###  option deadline, an online Enrollment Exception must be          ###
   ###  submitted. Approval of enrollment exception requests is not      ###
   ###  automatic. Students should be prepared to submit documentation   ###
   ###  for any enrollment exception request. For more information:      ###
   ###  https://www.reg.uci.edu/enrollment/adc/exceptions.html           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: Prerequisites are strictly enforced. The School   ###
   ###  WILL DROP students from courses for which they have not          ###
   ###  satisfied prerequisites. If you find you have been dropped from  ###
   ###  a course, please check the course prerequisites and contact the  ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs Office                                       ###
   ###  (http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/index.php) BEFORE enrolling in ###
   ###  the course again. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a space in the class.                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT RESTRICTION: Students are not allowed to repeat a course  ###
   ###  if they previously received a grade of C or better.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DISCUSSIONS & LABS: Unless otherwise specified by the course     ###
   ###  instructor, discussion and lab sections begin meeting AFTER the  ###
   ###  first lecture.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate students  ###
   ###  may enroll in undergraduate courses with permission and pending  ###
   ###  availability of seating.  Graduate students enrolled without     ###
   ###  prior approval will be dropped.                                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students may enroll in graduate level courses with the           ###
   ###  instructor's consent, if seats are available. No graduate course ###
   ###  taken as an undergraduate will count toward a graduate degree    ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION DEADLINE: The Donald Bren School of ###
   ###  Information and Computer Sciences STRICTLY adheres to the campus ###
   ###  deadline of 5:00pm on Friday of Week 2 for both undergraduate    ###
   ###  AND graduate level courses.                                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Enrollment Exception Requests: After the add/drop/change grade   ###
   ###  option deadline, an online Enrollment Exception must be          ###
   ###  submitted. Approval of enrollment exception requests is not      ###
   ###  automatic. Students should be prepared to submit documentation   ###
   ###  for any enrollment exception request. For more information:      ###
   ###  https://www.reg.uci.edu/enrollment/adc/exceptions.html           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: Prerequisites are strictly enforced. The School   ###
   ###  WILL DROP students from courses for which they have not          ###
   ###  satisfied prerequisites. If you find you have been dropped from  ###
   ###  a course, please check the course prerequisites and contact the  ###
   ###  ICS Student Affairs Office                                       ###
   ###  (http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/index.php) BEFORE enrolling in ###
   ###  the course again. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a space in the class.                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT RESTRICTION: Students are not allowed to repeat a course  ###
   ###  if they previously received a grade of C or better.              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DISCUSSIONS & LABS: Unless otherwise specified by the course     ###
   ###  instructor, discussion and lab sections begin meeting AFTER the  ###
   ###  first lecture.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate students  ###
   ###  may enroll in undergraduate courses with permission and pending  ###
   ###  availability of seating.  Graduate students enrolled without     ###
   ###  prior approval will be dropped.                                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students may enroll in graduate level courses with the           ###
   ###  instructor's consent, if seats are available. No graduate course ###
   ###  taken as an undergraduate will count toward a graduate degree    ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                                 Management

        RESTRICTIONS: Due to the high volume of majors, enrollment in
        most Paul Merage School of Business undergraduate courses will
        be restricted to majors only until Thursday, March 10, 2016 at
        noon. Some courses will remain major restricted.

        PREREQUISITES: If you received AP credit or transferred courses
        that are considered a prerequisite, please go to the Paul Merage
        School Undergraduate Programs Office located in SB1, Suite 5400
        to be cleared to enroll in the desired course.

                               Management MBA

        DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Paul Merage School of
        Business is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in
        WebReg.

        ADD: MBA Core classes are restricted to MBA students only.
        Non-MBA graduate students interested in adding a MBA elective
        course may contact the FTMBA Program Office located in SB1,
        Suite 4500 or email sofia.dang@uci.edu. The deadline to add
        courses in the Paul Merage School of Business is the end of Week
        2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.

        RESTRICTIONS: MBA elective classes are closed to non-MBA
        students unless otherwise authorized.

        PREREQUISITES: Vary by class. Please check with the FTMBA
        Program Office in SB1, Suite 4500 or email sofia.dang@uci.edu.

                                  Chemistry

        IMPORTANT: Please refer to WebSOC frequently for updates
        concerning course changes.  Please visit the Chemistry
        Department Undergraduate Program Office website at
        http://www.chem.uci.edu/undergrad for additional information on
        Chemistry undergraduate course enrollment procedures and
        frequently asked questions.

        DROP OR CHANGE: The deadline to drop courses or change the grade
        option or variable units in the School of  Physical Sciences is
        the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops or Changes can be made in
        WebReg until the end of week 2.

        ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Department of Chemistry
        without permission using WebReg is the end of  week 2 by 5:00PM.

        NO CHEMISTRY LABORATORY CHANGES AFTER WEEK 1.

        Please NOTE: This deadline is earlier than the School of
        Physical Sciences week 2 deadline.

        PREREQUISITES: Can't access Chemistry courses? Have transfer
        credit or took the equivalent at another institution for a Chem
        course? Fax or email, or bring a copy of your transcript or
        course confirmation to the Chemistry Undergraduate Program
        Office in NS2 1101 in order to clear the prerequisite prior to
        your enrollment. (Email: undergrad@chem.ps.uci.edu; Fax:
        949.824.8571). You may also be asked to provide a course
        syllabus.

        If you don't meet the prerequisites for the course, you will be
        dropped from the course by the Chemistry Department.

        WAITLIST:  Placement on the waitlist does not guarantee
        enrollment in the class. If you are unable to add through the
        waitlist system, you must register in an open section using
        WebReg by the enrollment deadline.  Visit
        http://www.reg.uci.edu/registrar/waitlist.html for more
        information regarding the waitlist system.

        REPEAT STUDENTS:

        1)Students will not have access to the chemistry course they
        wish to repeat when their enrollment window opens.

        2) The same course may not be repeated more than once during the
        academic year.

        3) Receive a D+, D, D-, F, NR, NP grade? Enroll on the first day
        of classes, Monday, March 28, 2016, beginning at 12:00pm.

        4) Receive a C-? Enroll on the third day of classes, Wednesday,
        March 30, 2016, beginning at 12:00pm.

        IMPORTANT LABORATORY INFORMATION.

        LAB FEES ARE NON-REFUNDABLE.

        1) All Chemistry Lab courses are charged a $50.00 lab fee. If
        you switch sections during the first week of classes, be sure
        you officially change your enrollment before 5pm Friday, April
        1, 2016; otherwise, you may be double- billed for the lab fee.
        No lab fee reversals will be considered after the quarter ends.

        Exception: The Spring quarter Chem 177L lab fee is $75.00.

        2) Safety goggles, lab aprons, and nitrile gloves. Refer to the
        following web sites for announcements:

        Chem 2L website: http://faculty.sites.uci.edu/chem2l

        Chem 51L website: http://sites.uci.edu/chem51labs

        Chem 52L website: http://sites.uci.edu/chem52labs

        3) If you do not attend your first laboratory session, you will
        receive a zero grade for that week and lose your space in the
        section.

        CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT is REQUIRED for chemistry courses. Enroll
        in a Chemistry lecture, a discussion associated with that
        specific lecture, a Chemistry laboratory, and a laboratory
        lecture or lab discussion when applicable. (Exception: Unless
        otherwise stated or if you have prior credit for lecture or
        laboratory. If you are uncertain about the requirements for your
        major, refer to an academic advisor in your major). Attendance
        for week 1 is mandatory.

        Courses with co-requisites may require you to add the
        co-requisite requirement before adding the course.

      ~    Biology, Chemistry, Engineering, Nursing Science, Pharmaceutical
      ~    Sciences, Physical Science, Public Health Sciences, and
      ~    Undecided/Undeclared. The MAJOR restriction may be lifted on March
      ~    18, 2016, by 12:00pm. If so, WebReg will allow other majors to
      ~    enroll after that time. The REPEAT restriction may be lifted during
      ~    the first week of the quarter. If so, WebReg will allow repeat
      ~    students to enroll.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                  Chemistry

        IMPORTANT: Please refer to WebSOC frequently for updates
        concerning course changes.  Please visit the Chemistry
        Department Undergraduate Program Office website at
        http://www.chem.uci.edu/undergrad for additional information on
        Chemistry undergraduate course enrollment procedures and
        frequently asked questions.

        DROP OR CHANGE: The deadline to drop courses or change the grade
        option or variable units in the School of  Physical Sciences is
        the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops or Changes can be made in
        WebReg until the end of week 2.

        ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Department of Chemistry
        without permission using WebReg is the end of  week 2 by 5:00PM.

        NO CHEMISTRY LABORATORY CHANGES AFTER WEEK 1.

        Please NOTE: This deadline is earlier than the School of
        Physical Sciences week 2 deadline.

        PREREQUISITES: Can't access Chemistry courses? Have transfer
        credit or took the equivalent at another institution for a Chem
        course? Fax or email, or bring a copy of your transcript or
        course confirmation to the Chemistry Undergraduate Program
        Office in NS2 1101 in order to clear the prerequisite prior to
        your enrollment. (Email: undergrad@chem.ps.uci.edu; Fax:
        949.824.8571). You may also be asked to provide a course
        syllabus.

        If you don't meet the prerequisites for the course, you will be
        dropped from the course by the Chemistry Department.

        WAITLIST:  Placement on the waitlist does not guarantee
        enrollment in the class. If you are unable to add through the
        waitlist system, you must register in an open section using
        WebReg by the enrollment deadline.  Visit
        http://www.reg.uci.edu/registrar/waitlist.html for more
        information regarding the waitlist system.

        REPEAT STUDENTS:

        1)Students will not have access to the chemistry course they
        wish to repeat when their enrollment window opens.

        2) The same course may not be repeated more than once during the
        academic year.

        3) Receive a D+, D, D-, F, NR, NP grade? Enroll on the first day
        of classes, Monday, March 28, 2016, beginning at 12:00pm.

        4) Receive a C-? Enroll on the third day of classes, Wednesday,
        March 30, 2016, beginning at 12:00pm.

        IMPORTANT LABORATORY INFORMATION.

        LAB FEES ARE NON-REFUNDABLE.

        1) All Chemistry Lab courses are charged a $50.00 lab fee. If
        you switch sections during the first week of classes, be sure
        you officially change your enrollment before 5pm Friday, April
        1, 2016; otherwise, you may be double- billed for the lab fee.
        No lab fee reversals will be considered after the quarter ends.

        Exception: The Spring quarter Chem 177L lab fee is $75.00.

        2) Safety goggles, lab aprons, and nitrile gloves. Refer to the
        following web sites for announcements:

        Chem 2L website: http://faculty.sites.uci.edu/chem2l

        Chem 51L website: http://sites.uci.edu/chem51labs

        Chem 52L website: http://sites.uci.edu/chem52labs

        3) If you do not attend your first laboratory session, you will
        receive a zero grade for that week and lose your space in the
        section.

        CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT is REQUIRED for chemistry courses. Enroll
        in a Chemistry lecture, a discussion associated with that
        specific lecture, a Chemistry laboratory, and a laboratory
        lecture or lab discussion when applicable. (Exception: Unless
        otherwise stated or if you have prior credit for lecture or
        laboratory. If you are uncertain about the requirements for your
        major, refer to an academic advisor in your major). Attendance
        for week 1 is mandatory.

        Courses with co-requisites may require you to add the
        co-requisite requirement before adding the course.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Chem course numbers 201 - 399:
  ~ Graduate Students: Choose the letter grade option for
  ~     the core graduate courses. If you choose to take
  ~     an additional course for the S/U option, contact
  ~     the professor of the course.
  ~ Chem 299 enrollment requires permission from the
  ~     instructor.
  ~ Undergraduate students who want to enroll in graduate
  ~     level courses: Contact the faculty member to
  ~     obtain permission before your enrollment window
  ~     opens. Students will have access to the course on
  ~     WebReg once the instructor sends the notification
  ~     of approval to the Chemistry Undergraduate
  ~     Office. Unauthorized undergraduate students will
  ~     be dropped from the course.
  ~ No undergraduates will be allowed in Chem 233
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

                                 Mathematics

        Refer to
        http://math.uci.edu/undergrad-courses/course-registration-and-placement-information##3
        for the Department's Add/Drop and Waitlist Policy. Many sections
        will fill to capacity, so plan schedules carefully.

        WARNING: Being on the electronic waitlist does NOT guarantee you
        a seat in the course.

        IMPORTANT: Refer to
        http://math.uci.edu/undergrad-courses/course-registration-and-placement-information#Top
        for additional information on Mathematics undergraduate course
        enrollment procedures. Graduate students have last priority in
        enrollment in undergraduate courses.

        REPEAT STUDENTS: You will NOT have access to lower-division Math
        courses you wish to repeat when your enrollment window opens. If
        your grade was an F, enroll on March 19, as space permits, via
        WebReg. If your grade was between a C- and D-, enroll on the
        first day of class, as space permits, via WebReg. An alternative
        is to retake the class in Summer Session.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                 Mathematics

        Refer to
        http://math.uci.edu/undergrad-courses/course-registration-and-placement-information##3
        for the Department's Add/Drop and Waitlist Policy. Many sections
        will fill to capacity, so plan schedules carefully.

        WARNING: Being on the electronic waitlist does NOT guarantee you
        a seat in the course.

        IMPORTANT: Refer to
        http://math.uci.edu/undergrad-courses/course-registration-and-placement-information#Top
        for additional information on Mathematics undergraduate course
        enrollment procedures. Graduate students have last priority in
        enrollment in undergraduate courses.

        REPEAT STUDENTS: You will NOT have access to lower-division Math
        courses you wish to repeat when your enrollment window opens. If
        your grade was an F, enroll on March 19, as space permits, via
        WebReg. If your grade was between a C- and D-, enroll on the
        first day of class, as space permits, via WebReg. An alternative
        is to retake the class in Summer Session.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Physics

        Please refer to the WebSOC frequently for updates concerning
        course changes, including adds, cancellations, and day/time/room
        adjustments. Please also visit
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/ugrad/affairs for answers to
        frequently asked questions.

        ADDS/DROPS FOR PHYSICS COURSES 1 THROUGH 61:

        DROP LECTURE, DISCUSSION & LAB: The deadline to drop any Physics
        course is Friday, April 8, 2016 (the end of Week 2). Drops must
        be made using WebReg. Students wishing to drop a course after
        that date must submit an Enrollment Exception via StudentAccess
        and obtain the required approval of the Dean of student's major.
        Note that approval is NOT guaranteed and is usually only granted
        in extreme emergencies.

        ADD LAB: The deadline to add a Physics Lab is Friday, April 8,
        2016 (the end of Week 2). Adds must be made using WebReg.

        ADD LECTURE AND DISCUSSION: The deadline to add a Physics
        Lecture and Discussion is Friday, April 8, 2016 (the end of week
        2). Adds must be made using WebReg. NO ADDS WILL BE ALLOWED
        AFTER THIS DATE.

        Students who wish to make a grade option change before April 8,
        2016 (the end of Week 2) should do so via WebReg. Students
        wishing to make a grade option change after that date must
        submit an Enrollment Exception via StudentAccess. Required
        approval is by the Dean of the student's major; approval is NOT
        guaranteed. Send enrollment questions to physics.enroll@uci.edu.

        STUDENTS WHO FAIL TO FILE AN OFFICIAL DROP WILL RECEIVE A GRADE
        OF "NR" IN THE COURSE. AN "NR" TURNS TO AN "F" OR "NP" AFTER ONE
        QUARTER OF ATTENDANCE.

        DISCUSSION SECTIONS:

        1. The Physics Tutoring Center is available to students in
        Physics 3, 7, 51, and 61. Please check
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/tutoring-schedule for scheduling.

        2. Enrollment in lecture and discussion is required. Most
        sections fill to capacity so students should plan their
        schedules carefully and enroll as early as possible using
        WebReg. See above for information on how to add/drop a
        discussion section.

        3. Attendance in your assigned discussion section is MANDATORY
        throughout the quarter. No quizzes or exams will be graded for
        students who do not attend their assigned section.

        LABORATORY SECTIONS:

        1. Memorial Day will be observed on Monday, May 30, 2016. All
        lab meetings missed due to the observance of Memorial Day are
        re-scheduled for Saturday, June 4, 2016 at the regular time.

        2. Most sections fill to capacity so students should plan their
        schedules carefully and enroll as early as possible using
        WebReg. See above for information on how to add/drop a
        laboratory section.

        3. Attendance in your assigned laboratory section is MANDATORY
        throughout the quarter. Students will be allowed to participate
        in their assigned sections only.

        4. Lab manuals for Physics 3LB-LC, 7LD and 52A-B-C are available
        at the UCI Bookstore. Courses 3LB-LC and 52A-B-C also require
        the use of 5 blue books (grid) which must be purchased prior to
        WEEK ONE at the UCI Bookstore.

        5. LAB FEES: Students of Physics 3LB-LC, 7LC-LD, 52A-B-C, 121W
        and 206 will be charged a $25 lab fee. The charges for these
        classes will be added to your ZOT Bill Week 1 of the quarter.
        These charges will be posted Week 3 if you add a Physics lab
        after week one. The last day to add a lab is Friday, April 8,
        2016 (the end of Week 2). Students who drop a Physics lab course
        no later than April 8, 2016 may have the fee reversed. In order
        to reverse the lab fee, students must bring proof of the drop
        date and their Student ID card to FRH 4109, hours 9-12pm Monday
        through Friday.

        PREREQUISITES:

        Physics 3 courses must be taken sequentially: 3A, 3B, 3C.

        USING THE WAITLIST SYSYEM: The waitlist system for all Physics
        courses will be activated through Friday of second week.
        Placement on the waitlist does not guarantee enrollment in the
        class. Students still on the waitlist after the end of week 2
        will not be added via the waitlist system. If you are unable to
        add through the waitlist system, you must add an open section
        using WebReg by the end of Week 2.

        Visit http://www.reg.uci.edu/enrollment/waitlistoption.html for
        more information regarding the waitlist system.

        Undergraduate students enrolling in Physics Graduate Classes

        Undergraduates may take Physics courses numbered 200 and higher
        provided (1) their overall GPA is 3.0 or better, (2) their GPA
        in Physics courses is 3.5 or better, (3) they have the approval
        of the Physics Dept Undergraduate Committee and (4) approval of
        the Department's Committee on Graduate Affairs.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Physics

        Please refer to the WebSOC frequently for updates concerning
        course changes, including adds, cancellations, and day/time/room
        adjustments. Please also visit
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/ugrad/affairs for answers to
        frequently asked questions.

        ADDS/DROPS FOR PHYSICS COURSES 1 THROUGH 61:

        DROP LECTURE, DISCUSSION & LAB: The deadline to drop any Physics
        course is Friday, April 8, 2016 (the end of Week 2). Drops must
        be made using WebReg. Students wishing to drop a course after
        that date must submit an Enrollment Exception via StudentAccess
        and obtain the required approval of the Dean of student's major.
        Note that approval is NOT guaranteed and is usually only granted
        in extreme emergencies.

        ADD LAB: The deadline to add a Physics Lab is Friday, April 8,
        2016 (the end of Week 2). Adds must be made using WebReg.

        ADD LECTURE AND DISCUSSION: The deadline to add a Physics
        Lecture and Discussion is Friday, April 8, 2016 (the end of week
        2). Adds must be made using WebReg. NO ADDS WILL BE ALLOWED
        AFTER THIS DATE.

        Students who wish to make a grade option change before April 8,
        2016 (the end of Week 2) should do so via WebReg. Students
        wishing to make a grade option change after that date must
        submit an Enrollment Exception via StudentAccess. Required
        approval is by the Dean of the student's major; approval is NOT
        guaranteed. Send enrollment questions to physics.enroll@uci.edu.

        STUDENTS WHO FAIL TO FILE AN OFFICIAL DROP WILL RECEIVE A GRADE
        OF "NR" IN THE COURSE. AN "NR" TURNS TO AN "F" OR "NP" AFTER ONE
        QUARTER OF ATTENDANCE.

        DISCUSSION SECTIONS:

        1. The Physics Tutoring Center is available to students in
        Physics 3, 7, 51, and 61. Please check
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/tutoring-schedule for scheduling.

        2. Enrollment in lecture and discussion is required. Most
        sections fill to capacity so students should plan their
        schedules carefully and enroll as early as possible using
        WebReg. See above for information on how to add/drop a
        discussion section.

        3. Attendance in your assigned discussion section is MANDATORY
        throughout the quarter. No quizzes or exams will be graded for
        students who do not attend their assigned section.

        LABORATORY SECTIONS:

        1. Memorial Day will be observed on Monday, May 30, 2016. All
        lab meetings missed due to the observance of Memorial Day are
        re-scheduled for Saturday, June 4, 2016 at the regular time.

        2. Most sections fill to capacity so students should plan their
        schedules carefully and enroll as early as possible using
        WebReg. See above for information on how to add/drop a
        laboratory section.

        3. Attendance in your assigned laboratory section is MANDATORY
        throughout the quarter. Students will be allowed to participate
        in their assigned sections only.

        4. Lab manuals for Physics 3LB-LC, 7LD and 52A-B-C are available
        at the UCI Bookstore. Courses 3LB-LC and 52A-B-C also require
        the use of 5 blue books (grid) which must be purchased prior to
        WEEK ONE at the UCI Bookstore.

        5. LAB FEES: Students of Physics 3LB-LC, 7LC-LD, 52A-B-C, 121W
        and 206 will be charged a $25 lab fee. The charges for these
        classes will be added to your ZOT Bill Week 1 of the quarter.
        These charges will be posted Week 3 if you add a Physics lab
        after week one. The last day to add a lab is Friday, April 8,
        2016 (the end of Week 2). Students who drop a Physics lab course
        no later than April 8, 2016 may have the fee reversed. In order
        to reverse the lab fee, students must bring proof of the drop
        date and their Student ID card to FRH 4109, hours 9-12pm Monday
        through Friday.

        PREREQUISITES:

        Physics 3 courses must be taken sequentially: 3A, 3B, 3C.

        USING THE WAITLIST SYSYEM: The waitlist system for all Physics
        courses will be activated through Friday of second week.
        Placement on the waitlist does not guarantee enrollment in the
        class. Students still on the waitlist after the end of week 2
        will not be added via the waitlist system. If you are unable to
        add through the waitlist system, you must add an open section
        using WebReg by the end of Week 2.

        Visit http://www.reg.uci.edu/enrollment/waitlistoption.html for
        more information regarding the waitlist system.

        Undergraduate students enrolling in Physics Graduate Classes

        Undergraduates may take Physics courses numbered 200 and higher
        provided (1) their overall GPA is 3.0 or better, (2) their GPA
        in Physics courses is 3.5 or better, (3) they have the approval
        of the Physics Dept Undergraduate Committee and (4) approval of
        the Department's Committee on Graduate Affairs.

   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Ecology is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM.                                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL & MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at http://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###

   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/field-study                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###

SocEcol  195       FIELD STUDY
      ~ Social Ecology 195, Field Study enrollment requires that students have
      ~    formally accepted a placement offer from a field study site and
      ~    submitted a course enrollment form by the appropriate deadline. For
      ~    more information about the process and deadlines to apply to Field
      ~    Study go to http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/field-study, then
      ~    click on the link for Field Study Schedule with Procedures. Students
      ~    enrolling for the quarter must have already accepted a placement
      ~    with a field study community partner.
      ~ Field study is P/NP only and is a variable unit course.  Input the
      ~    appropriate number of units in the unit box (1 unit/25 hours of
      ~    field work).
      ~ The Field Study Areas listed below reflect faculty departmental
      ~    affiliations and provide students with a general guideline with
      ~    which to select a Field Study course section.  It is recommended
      ~    (but NOT required) that students match their field placement site
      ~    with a course section in the appropriate area.
      ~ Section A is reserved for those accepted into Advance Field Study
      ~ B sections are reserved for those accepted in the Blum Center Immersion
      ~    Field Study
      ~ C sections are CLS faculty
      ~ U sections are PP&D Faculty
      ~ P sections are Psy Beh Faculty
    CCode Typ Sec Unt Instructor      Time              Place     Final                     Max     Enr Req Rstr Status

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Ecology                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Ecology is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM.                                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL & MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at http://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/field-study                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until March 14th.                                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Ecology is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM.                                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL & MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at http://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/field-study                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until March 14th.                                                ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Ecology                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Ecology is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM.                                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL & MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at http://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/field-study                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until March 14th.                                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Ecology                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Ecology is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM.                                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL & MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at http://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/field-study                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until March 14th.                                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###

   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For most courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact   ###
   ###  the instructor of the course.                                    ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For most courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact   ###
   ###  the instructor of the course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  NEW ITEM to view:  EaterEvals available to view at               ###
   ###  https://eaterevals.eee.uci.edu                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                                  Economics

        Departmental drop/add policy

        Drops

        Students may drop Economics courses only through the second week
        of the quarter. After the second week, permission to drop will
        NOT be granted by the instructor.

        Adds

        The Department of Economics' policy on adds remains unchanged,
        and follows that of the School of Social Sciences. For more
        information please visit the website:
        http://www.economics.uci.edu/index.php?p=37
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For most courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact   ###
   ###  the instructor of the course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  NEW ITEM to view:  EaterEvals available to view at               ###
   ###  https://eaterevals.eee.uci.edu                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For most courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact   ###
   ###  the instructor of the course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  https://eaterevals.eee.uci.edu                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                       Logic and Philosophy of Science

        Enrollment in both lecture and discussion (where offered) is
        required of all LPS courses unless otherwise indicated. Choose
        discussion directly below lecture.

        Course offerings/times/days/locations are subject to change
        without notice. Check WebSOC for latest updates.

   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For most courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact   ###
   ###  the instructor of the course.                                    ###

   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###

   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For most courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact   ###
   ###  the instructor of the course.                                    ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For most courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact   ###

Soc Sci 10 courses:
  ~ Soc Sci 10A-B-C, You must continue in the same
  ~     lecture each quarter (i.e., if you are in Soc Sci
  ~     10A Lecture A in fall, you must select Soc Sci
  ~     10B Lecture A in winter and Soc Sci 10C Lecture A
  ~     in spring). Lab is required.
  ~ Authorization codes are required to enroll in Soc Sci
  ~     10C.

   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-6 must be made through Student Access.   ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Dean's signature can be obtained in the Social Sciences          ###
   ###  Undergraduate Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG.       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Restrictions on courses in the School of Social Sciences will be ###
   ###  lifted by noon on March 11th.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you received AP credit or transferred courses that is         ###
   ###  considered a pre-req, please go to Social Sciences Undergraduate ###
   ###  Student Affairs Office located in 1201 SBSG to be cleared to     ###
   ###  enroll in the desired course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For most courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact   ###
   ###  the instructor of the course.                                    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  NEW ITEM to view:  EaterEvals available to view at               ###
   ###  https://eaterevals.eee.uci.edu                                   ###
