   ###  LARC tutorials are lecture-specific.  Go to the LARC website     ###
   ###  (http://www.larc.uci.edu) to make sure you are enrolled in the   ###
   ###  correct tutorial for your lecture.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  LARC will use your UCI email to communicate with you about       ###
   ###  critical information.  Please be sure to activate your UCInetID  ###
   ###  (http://www.nacs.uci.edu/email/).                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP POLICY:  You may be dropped if you do not attend the first  ###
   ###  tutorial meeting.  Tutorials begin on the Wednesday of Week 1 of ###
   ###  classes. (http://www.larc.uci.edu/fees.html)                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  WAIT LIST POLICY:  You cannot attend a LARC session while on the ###
   ###  waitlist.                                                        ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                              Campus Recreation

        All Campus Recreation Activity classes are scheduled to start on
        Monday, March 28.

        Participants must register and pay for classes through Campus
        Recreation website or ARC Service Desk. Enrollment through
        WebReg is not an official enrollment in the class.

        All activity classes are offered without credit through the
        Department of Campus Recreation.  For fee based classes, please
        contact the Anteater Recreation Center for a complete fee
        schedule.

        Some classes do not meet the full 10 week session, please check
        with Campus Recreation Services Desk for additional information.

        The first session of each class will meet at the Anteater
        Recreation Center. For Stand-up Paddle Board and Kayaking class
        locations please pick-up directions at the Campus Recreation
        Services Desk.  Students must pay activity fees prior to the
        first meeting in order to guarantee their place in class.

        Sailing and Stand-up Paddle Board classes will take place at the
        new Marina Park facility. Please contact the ARC Service Desk
        for more information.

Uni Stu 3 courses:
  ~ Enrollment in Uni Stu 3 courses will be restricted to
  ~     freshmen until the day the 18-unit enrollment
  ~     limit is lifted. Freshmen with sophomore standing
  ~     may request an exception to allow them to enroll.
  ~ After the freshman-only date, enrollment in Uni Stu 3
  ~     will be open to all lower-division
  ~     undergraduates. For more information on Freshman
  ~     Seminars, see the website at
  ~     http://www.freshmanseminar.uci.edu or call the
  ~     Undecided/Undeclared Advising Program at
  ~     949-824-6987.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

       _________________________________________________________________

                           Pharmaceutical Sciences

        PREREQUISITES: Students who have completed the equivalent of the
        prerequisites at another institution may verify eligibility to
        enroll in a particular UCI PhrmSci course by emailing
        pharmsci@uci.edu a minimum of two days before their registration
        window opens.

        LAB COURSES:

        PHARM SCI LAB ENROLLMENT POLICY!!!!!

        THERE WILL BE NO DROPS ALLOWED OF ANY PHARM SCI UPPER-DIVISION
        LABS AFTER MARCH 27 (DAY BEFORE CLASSES BEGIN)

        This deadline is earlier than the College of Health Sciences
        week 2 deadline.

        Lab fees of $75 are non-refundable. Deadline to pay lab fee is
        Friday of week 3.

        Live vertebrate animals are preserved animal tissue will be used
        in this lab course. Please do not register for the course if you
        have reservations about engaging in lab projects of this kind.

        MINIMUM GRADE POLICY

        Beginning Fall 2010, students must earn a grade of "C-" or above
        to advance to the next PhrmSci core course. For example, you
        must earn a "C-" or better grade in PhrmSci 170A to move on to
        PhrmSci 170B.

       _________________________________________________________________

                                Public Health

        Public Health course offerings/times/days/locations are subject
        to change without notice. Check WEBSOC for latest updates.

        IMPORTANT: Refer to the Public Health Student Services Office or
        the Public Health website at: http://publichealth.uci.edu/ for
        additional information on Public Health course enrollment
        procedures and frequently asked questions, policies, and contact
        information.

        PREREQUISITES: Prerequisites may be cleared ahead of your
        registration date. Please e-mail Public Health Undergraduate
        Student Affairs at: phuao@uci.edu a minimum of one week before
        your registration window opens.

        REMINDERS: Courses must be taken for a letter grade to fulfill
        major requirements. Enrollment in discussion or lab may be
        required in addition to lecture. Choose from discussion or lab
        sections listed directly below the lecture.

        PRACTICUM: Students are encouraged to begin planning for
        Practicum two quarters in advance. For more information and
        important deadlines, visit:
        http://publichealth.uci.edu/admin//practicum_undergrad#.
        Undergraduate students contact Public Health Undergraduate
        Student Affairs at: phuao@uci.edu. Graduate students contact
        Public Health Graduate Student Affairs at: phgo@uci.edu.

        MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in
        some Public Health courses will be restricted to Public Health
        majors only. Major restrictions will be lifted on March 18, 2016
        at noon.

        AUTHORIZATION CODES: Contact instructor or phuao@uci.edu, unless
        otherwise noted.

        WAITLIST: Placement on the waitlist does not guarantee
        enrollment in the class.
